<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09037</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO INSTITUTIONALIZE DEPLOYMENT OF TEACHER TO THE BARRIOS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to address the problem of accessibility to basic education through the institutionalization of a Teacher to the Barrios program for the DepEd to provide basic education to the pupils/students in 
geographically isolated communities.

Proposes to create a program, whereby teachers shall be deployed to remote, far-flung areas to educate these children with a parallel module to that of a formal basic education in a form of study session, which may be conducted in a public community hall, or a private hall/place.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>PICO, PEPITO M.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-02-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2019-02-07</td></tr></table>